Pills are the palette's persistent state. Each strip is a separate concern, sits in its own row, and uses the same push / DEL / Tab-cycle grammar.

! The six strips

|!Strip |!Concern |!Activation |!Mutual exclusion |
|''Preset'' |Snapshot every other strip's state and recall it as one |Leaders `s` (save) and `r` (recall) |No — one preset can be "active" but stacking presets is meaningless |
|''Filter'' |Narrow which rows the engine considers |Leader `>` (push by title) or `+` picker pill |No |
|''Visibility'' |Hide whole entry groups via filter |`v` leaders set by tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/visibility` |No |
|''View'' |Switch between alternate trees of the same data |Leader (one per view) |Yes — exactly one view active |
|''Reach'' |Where to search (here vs. whole tree) |Leaders `d` (Here) and `g` (Everywhere) |Yes — pushing one evicts the other |
|''Search-in'' |Which fields the matcher reads |Leader `a` (all) or individual leaders per field |No — pills accumulate (union semantics) |

! Plus: the Structure strip

Below the view strip sits a ''Structure'' strip (only visible when the active view declares channels). Tab into it, Enter / → to expand into the view→channel tree: a ''view'' header row leading with three lens choosers (Name / Icon / Note — the view's default row decorations; ''`l`'' toggles a lock) and one indented ''channel'' mini-row each. A channel's mini-row leads with its own three lens choosers (overriding or inheriting the view default), then its primitive pills (roots / children / leaf / label / row decorations) AND its ''axis chain'' as yellow ''by'' / ''→'' pills + a dashed ''+'' pill to append. Lens choosers cycle on ↵/Space, the axis chain edits live (Backspace removes, Shift-←/→ reorders, Enter swaps); the remaining primitive pills are read-only here (edit them via ''Manage views → Edit all fields…''). The view header and each explicit channel mini-row also carry a ''summary'' pill — the Overview-row template (`ca-view-preview` / `ca-channel-preview`): ↵ edits it, DEL clears it, ''—'' shows when unset.

See <$link to="$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/help/axes">Axes</$link> for the axis grammar and edit gestures.

! Common grammar

* Pills appear as text chips with an `×` close button.
* `Tab` cycles focus into a strip; `←` / `→` move along the strip.
* `DEL` on a focused pill removes it.
* `Ctrl-DEL` clears the whole strip.
* When NO pill is pushed, the strip is hidden (no visual clutter).

! Discoverability

Pills are discoverable by their leader keys (see ''Keys'' section). Leaders that push pills are tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/leader` and live in `dev-wiki/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/leaders/`.

''→'' Full pill semantics: <$link to="$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/doc/protocol">doc/protocol</$link>
